Apparently, [Olympia, Washington](/Olympia,_Washington) in 1993 was fertile ground for *something*. It was there, amidst whatever mundane happenings typically fill such places, that [Team Dresch](/Team_Dresch), an American [punk rock](/Punk_rock) outfit, decided to coalesce. &#91;1&#93; A decision, one assumes, they've been committed to, on and off, ever since. They are primarily known for their pioneering role within the [queercore](/Queercore) movement, a subgenre that, much like the band itself, refused to be ignored, blending raw musical aggression with explicit queer identity and political messaging.

